I have generated the keyed TransactOpts object, and also created the ABI function file from the multicall contract above with abigen All of this is working correctly, butI can't call the contract and get the results because I don't know how to get the ABI string correctly formatted in the callData struct field

If I want to call getReserves, how do I format the ABI string correctly in to callData in order to complete the contract call execution ?

The easiest way to do it is to use the json abi of the calls that should be produced to automatically pack (with abigen)
You can also manually pack the callData like this: (However that is prone to errors)
```go
func main() {
    AddressArr, err := abi.NewType("address[]", "", nil)
    if err != nil {
        panic(err)
    }
    Uint256, err := abi.NewType("uint256", "", nil)
    if err != nil {
        panic(err)
    }
    Bool, err := abi.NewType("bool", "", nil)
    if err != nil {
        panic(err)
    }
    args := abi.Arguments{
        {Type: AddressArr},
        {Type: Uint256},
        {Type: Bool},
    }
    enc, err := args.Pack(
        []common.Address{
            common.HexToAddress("0x3403D13dF08EDB7eB03758c0cC2F800315835B00"),
            common.HexToAddress("0x366A0Ee2F0d6D51E5Ca2a5f8E7edfD74D02F6B3e"),
        },
        big.NewInt(1135234),
        false,
    )
    if err != nil {
        panic(err)
    }
    fmt.Println(hex.EncodeToString(enc))
}
```
